			<div class="content" id="post-content-2468760">
									

<p>Considering how vague my feedback was, I have to say that I think you've implemented it perfectly ;) This version has a much more discursive feel that brings the format to life - footnote 11 was a particular highlight. And it covers the fact that this is dealing with a bunch of links and moving pieces to set up for the finale - that is now very smooth.</p>
<p>On a second read, I do have a few questions:</p>
<ul>
<li>How does Rashid know that the Samsara squad are &quot;immortal constructs&quot;? Is it simply by &quot;divin[ing] what it was that attacked us&quot;?</li>
<li>If The Ascending Path is written in Arabic (as appears to be the case), how can Samsara squad read it?</li>
<li>Is Ulyana the Witch the same witch from &quot;Mistakes Were Made&quot;? My headcanon hopes so.</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
					
